**Critical insight:** Linear loss's 5/5 "secure" runs are deceptive — Eve's error is far ABOVE baseline (14 bits), meaning she's anti-correlated. An adversary who simply negates her output would get **~2 bits error** — near-perfect break!

**Bottom takeaway:** Only quadratic loss achieves genuine, interpretable security.

